->The DISTINCT keyword is crucial for retrieving unique values from a database column. It is more versatile as it works in both MySQL and Oracle, whereas UNIQUE is 
specific to Oracle for retrieval purposes. We provided an example query to demonstrate the usage of DISTINCT in finding distinct designations from a table.
